Enum ManhattanDirection

public enum ManhattanDirection
extends java.lang.Enum<ManhattanDirection>
implements java.io.Serializable

Represents a mathematical vector by storing a GridPoint that equals a direction. The GridPoint can be received by accessing a direction of this enum type.

Author:
Marc Rochow, Anja Radtke

calcDir

public static ManhattanDirection calcDir(GridPoint a,
                                         GridPoint b)
Calculates the direction. The Manhattan direction can only be "RIGHT" if the points are in the same row and only "DOWN" if the points are in the same column.

Parameters:
a - first GridPoint
b - second GridPoint
Returns:
the Manhattan direction of the two points.

orthogonalDir

public ManhattanDirection orthogonalDir()
Returns a direction, orthogonal to this direction in a clockwise order. The actual method is empty since it is overrided by each enum value.

Returns:
next Manhattan direction.
